place.name: HEMBLINGTON
place.gazetteerText: HEMBLINGTON, a parish in Blofield district, Norfolk; 3 miles NE by N of Brundall r. station, and 3½ WNW of Acle. Post town, Blofield, under Norwich. Acres, 739. Real property, £1, 730. Pop., 219. Houses, 47. Hemblington Hall is a chief residence. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £56. Patrons, the Dean and Chapter of Norwich. The church has a round tower, and is good. There is a national school. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
